ndust-to-gas ratio <A_V/N(HI)> ~ 2 to 4 x 10**(-23) mag cm^2. This value is ~\n-1.25 dex lower than the mean dust-to-gas ratio of the Milky Way, in line with\nthe lower level of metallicity in the present DLA sample.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 7 Dec 2007 10:37:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
