RLIN finds extended lobe emission on either side of\nthe main lensing galaxy. Therefore, the radio emission from the third radio\ncomponent is almost certainly from an AGN within the main lensing galaxy, which\nis classified as an FR I type radio source.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 7 Dec 2007 14:01:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
