ly to the second degree in eccentricity and inclination\n(obliquity). It can easily be extended to higher orders, but formal accuracy\nwill not be a real improvement as long as the physics of the processes leading\nto tidal lags is not better known.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 7 Dec 2007 15:12:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 19 Feb 2008 18:56:52 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 27 Apr 2009 12:55:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-06-19"}
